Distell, over the weekend, has unveiled its latest addition, 4th Street non-alcoholic wine, into the Nigerian market. The non-alcoholic sparkling wine, locally produced in Nigeria, is a first for the 4th Street brand across the Distell business in Africa. Speaking at the launch, the Managing Director of Distell Nigeria Limited, noted that the entire product from the content, to the packaging is locally sourced in Nigeria, and having gone through thorough research and quality proofing, is ready to be launched into the Nigerian market and for export. He explained that from research, it was revealed that After the COVID pandemic, wine business has grown rapidly because people are much more aware of their health and want healthier options of drinks, hence the introduction of the 4th Street non-alcoholic drink. Speaking of the choice of Nigeria to launch the product, Marketing Director, Distell Africa, Kushilla Thomas said the country has a huge population and vibrant youth that the brand resonates with as evident in the significant growth of the 4th Street brands in the country over the years. Vireshree Naidoo, the Marketing Lead, Distell West Africa  noted that the focus of the launch campaign is to position 4th Street’s new non-alcoholic sparkling wine as the drink of choice for young, upbeat, urban, and social Nigerians looking to celebrate their way, drink their way and at anytime. She explained that the company is set to roll out it’s Below-the Line (BTL) and Above-the-Line (ATL) activities to drive awareness and visibility of the product, as it strives to successfully build presence in the market.  ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
